Title(s): An Elegy on the deaths of Eleanor Cobham, John Beaufort and Duke Humphrey
Subjects: elegies; mutability; Humphrey, duke of Gloucester; Beaufort, John; Cobham, Eleanor; historical poems
_description: An Elegy on the deaths of Eleanor Cobham, John Beaufort and Duke Humphrey — eight 8-line stanzas

BodRawC813.First Lines:
Musyng vppon the mutabiliteoff worldlye changes and grett
                    vnstablenes…
BodRawC813.Last Lines:
…I toke hym Sone after and Soo lowe brought hym downethat In
                    shorte while after I caused hym to dye
